description.narrative: This activity (Humanitarian Surge Support) is a component of Building Resilience in Ethiopia (BRE) reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Multilateral organisation' and a budget of £2,550,245. This component benefits Ethiopia, and works in the following sector(s): Disaster prevention and preparedness. , with the following implementing partners: CANADEM, Crown Agents Limited, DAI Europe, IMC Worldwide, Palladium International Ltd (UK). The start date is 30-05-2017 and the end date is 31-05-2022.
